## 🧪 Edge Cases to Handle

| Input Scenario | Expected Behavior | Owner |
|---------------|-------------------|-------|
| Empty PDF | Clear error: "This PDF contains no extractable text" | M2 |
| Image-only PDF (scanned) | Error: "Scanned PDFs not supported. Please upload text-based PDF" | M2 |
| Very short paper (1-2 paragraphs) | Analyze but note: "Insufficient content for reliable stylometric analysis" | M1 |
| Very long paper (100+ pages) | Truncate to first 50 paragraphs with warning | M2 |
| Paper with no references | Skip citation analysis, flag as "No references found" | M2 |
| Non-academic text (e.g., novel) | Still analyze — system should work on any text | M1 |
| Non-English paper | Report: "Non-English text detected. Analysis optimized for English" | M1 |
| Corrupted/invalid PDF | Clear error: "Unable to parse this file. Please ensure it's a valid PDF" | M2 |
| Paper with genuinely one author | Report: "High consistency — likely single author" (this is the correct negative case) | M1 |
| Network/API failure | Show cached partial results + "Analysis incomplete — retry" | M4 |

