## 📝 Test Data Strategy

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **M5 must create test PDFs BEFORE the core system is done.** This is critical — you can't test without known-ground-truth documents.

### Test PDF #1: Genuine Paper (Single Author)
- Take any single-authored arxiv paper
- Expected result: "High consistency, likely single author, 1 estimated author"

### Test PDF #2: Stitched Paper (Multi-Author)
- Take introduction from Paper A, methodology from Paper B, results from Paper C
- Paste them into one document
- Expected result: "3 estimated authors, sections 2-3 and 4-5 flagged, style shifts detected"

### Test PDF #3: Collaborative Paper (Legitimate Multi-Author)
- Take a genuine multi-author paper but written coherently
- Expected result: "Some variation but overall consistent" — the system should NOT flag legitimate collaborations aggressively

