## ⚠️ Key Risks & Mitigations

| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |
|------|--------|-----------|
| **GPT-4 rate limits** | Analysis fails mid-pipeline | Batch paragraphs (5 at a time), add retry logic with exponential backoff |
| **GPT-4 cost overrun** | API key burns through budget | Use `gpt-4o-mini` for style metrics, reserve `gpt-4o` for final author estimation only |
| **PDF parsing inconsistency** | Garbled text breaks analysis | Use pdfplumber (better than PyPDF2 for layout), add text cleanup step |
| **Arxiv search is slow** | Demo stalls during source tracing | Cache results, make it async, show "searching..." with progress |
| **Style analysis not convincing** | Judges question accuracy | Combine GPT-4 analysis with actual NLP metrics (sentence length, vocab richness via code) — don't rely on GPT alone |
| **Heatmap looks basic** | Low visual impact | Use gradient colors, smooth transitions, click-to-expand detail panels |

---

## 💰 OpenAI API Cost Estimate

Assuming a 20-page paper with ~40 paragraphs:

| API Call | Count | Model | Est. Cost |
|----------|-------|-------|-----------|
| Style analysis per paragraph | 40 | gpt-4o-mini | ~$0.02 |
| Pairwise style comparison | 39 | gpt-4o-mini | ~$0.02 |
| Citation forensics | 1 | gpt-4o | ~$0.03 |
| Author count estimation | 1 | gpt-4o | ~$0.03 |
| Forensic report generation | 1 | gpt-4o | ~$0.05 |
| Embedding flagged sections | ~10 | text-embedding-3-small | ~$0.001 |
| Embedding arxiv abstracts | ~50 | text-embedding-3-small | ~$0.005 |
| **Total per analysis** | | | **~$0.15** |

> You can run **hundreds of analyses** during the hackathon without budget concerns. Use the API aggressively.

